{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b3b43c1-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s511"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"511"},"text":"§ 511.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"When used in this subchapter, unless the context indicates otherwise—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “alteration” includes changes of any kind, reconstruction, or removal in whole or in part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “bridge” means a lawful bridge over navigable waters of the United States, including approaches, fenders, and appurtenances thereto, which is used and operated for the purpose of carrying railroad traffic, or both railroad and highway traffic, or if a State, county, municipality, or other political subdivision is the owner or joint owner thereof, which is used and operated for the purpose of carrying highway traffic.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “bridge owner” means any State, county, municipality, or other political subdivision, or any corporation, association, partnership, or individual owning, or jointly owning, any bridge, and, when any bridge shall be in the possession or under the control of any trustee, receiver, trustee in a case under title 11, or lessee, such terms shall include both the owner of the legal title and the person or the entity in possession or control of such bridge.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the department in which the Coast Guard is operating.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “United States”, when used in a geographical sense, includes the Territories and possessions of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b3b43c2-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1940-06-21/ch409/s1"},"text":"June 21, 1940, ch. 409, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/54/497"},"text":"54 Stat. 497","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-16/ch889/s1"},"text":"July 16, 1952, ch. 889, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/732"},"text":"66 Stat. 732","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/tIII/s323"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598, title III, § 323","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2679"},"text":"92 Stat. 2679","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/449/s2/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–449, § 2(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1983-01-12"},"text":"Jan. 12, 1983","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/2440"},"text":"96 Stat. 2440","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120/tIII/s306/b/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120, title III, § 306(b)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-08"},"text":"Feb. 8, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/55"},"text":"130 Stat. 55","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b3b43c3-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b3b43c4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id6b3b43c5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2016—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/120"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–120","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Secretary of the department in which the Coast Guard is operating” for “Secretary of Transportation”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1983—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/449"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–449","children":[],"tail":" substituted provision that the term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Transportation for provision that it meant the Secretary of War acting directly or through the Chief of Engineers."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" substituted in definition of “bridge owner” the phrase “trustee in a case under title 11” for “trustee in bankruptcy”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1952—Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1952-07-16"},"text":"July 16, 1952","children":[],"tail":", redefined “bridge” and “bridge owner”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id6b3b43c6-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id6b3b43c7-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1978 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598/s402/a"},"text":"section 402(a) of Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Dates note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t11/s101"},"text":"section 101 of Title 11","children":[],"tail":", Bankruptcy."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id6b3b43c8-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 511 to 523 of this title are popularly known as the “Hobbs Bridge Act” and also as the “Truman-Hobbs Act”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id6b3b43c9-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/3"},"text":"Section 6(g)(3) of Pub. L. 89–670","children":[],"tail":" transferred functions, powers, and duties of Secretary of the Army [formerly War] and other officers and offices of Department of the Army [formerly War] relating to obstructive bridges under this subchapter to Secretary of Transportation. "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/449"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–449","children":[],"tail":" amended this section to reflect transfer made by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/670/s6/g/3"},"text":"section 6(g)(3) of Pub. L. 89–670","children":[],"tail":", and repealed section 6(g)(3)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
